sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ mTLS
    participant Manager as Operator Manager<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant AppWrapperCtrl as AppWrapper Controller
    participant RayCtrl as RayCluster Controller
    participant Kueue as Kueue Operator
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,KubeRay: Flow 1: AppWrapper Admission & Workload Scheduling

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply AppWrapper<br/>workload.codeflare.dev/v1beta2
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-workload-codeflare-dev-v1beta2-appwrapper<br/>mTLS (API server client cert)
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: GET/PATCH resources<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated AppWrapper
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-workload-codeflare-dev-v1beta2-appwrapper<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result
    K8sAPI-->>User: AppWrapper created

    AppWrapperCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch AppWrapper resources<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>AppWrapperCtrl: AppWrapper event

    AppWrapperCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Kueue Workload<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Kueue: Workload created event
    Kueue->>K8sAPI: Update Workload status (admitted)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+

    AppWrapperCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch Workload status<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>AppWrapperCtrl: Workload admitted

    AppWrapperCtrl->>K8sAPI: Deploy wrapped resources (RayCluster, etc)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,KubeRay: Flow 2: RayCluster Reconciliation

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayCluster<br/>ray.io/v1
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-ray-io-v1-raycluster<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated RayCluster (OAuth, mTLS injected)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-ray-io-v1-raycluster<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result

    RayCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch RayCluster resources<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>RayCtrl: RayCluster event

    RayCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    RayCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create CA Secret (for mTLS)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    RayCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    RayCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Route/Ingress<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    K8sAPI->>KubeRay: RayCluster reconciliation
    KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Deploy Ray Head and Worker Pods

    Note over User,KubeRay: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Manager: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    Manager-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics (operator health, reconciliation stats)

    Note over User,KubeRay: Flow 4: Health Checks

    K8sAPI->>Manager: GET /healthz<br/>HTTP/8081<br/>No Auth
    Manager-->>K8sAPI: OK (200)

    K8sAPI->>Manager: GET /readyz<br/>HTTP/8081<br/>No Auth
    Manager-->>K8sAPI: OK (200)

    Note over User,KubeRay: Flow 5: Ray Cluster mTLS Communication (Optional)

    User->>K8sAPI: Ray client connects to cluster
    K8sAPI-->>User: Ray Head Service endpoint

    User->>RayCtrl: Ray client → Ray Head<br/>10001/TCP HTTPS<br/>mTLS (Client Certificate)
    Note right of RayCtrl: Ray Worker → Ray Head<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>mTLS (Client Certificate)
